All Classes

Class Description
AlertPopUp
AlertPopUp class as type of POP_UP_SCREEN view when user makes any invalid operation.
Crate
Crate class as GameObject, possessing CrateStatus enumeration.
Crate.CrateStatus
CrateStatus enumeration defines all status of Crate object.
DataManager
DataManager class as game manager to take charge of recording high scores(timing and move count) of players for each levels.
Debugger
Debugger class is used as in-line debugging tool following the Debugging Guideline 4 introduced in lecture: Use Trace and Test Flags.
Diamond
Diamond class as GameObject.
EventManager
EventManager class as game manager to take charge of subscribe or unsubscribe any event handlers to current scene.
Floor
Floor class as GameObject.
GameEngine
GameEngine singleton class to take charge of all sectors of the running game by dispatching jobs to its attached managers and screen player.
GameManager
GameManager super class to be extended by all children managers.
GameObject
GameObject class as super class(parent) of all other GameObject in the game.
GameObjectFactory
GameObjectFactory class takes charge of generating specific GameObject by given type and position.
GameScreen
GameScreen class as super class(parent) of all other show-able GameScreens in the game.
GamingScreen
GamingScreen class as type of SCREEN view for user playing the game.
GamingScreenController
GamingScreenController class to register and handle event of the GamingScreen.
GraphicUnit
GraphicUnit class as factory to generate ImageView according GameObjects and their status.
GraphicUnitRenderer
GraphicUnitRenderer class takes charge of rendering graphic units of specific GameObjects on gaming screen.
Layer
Layer class as to store grids(2-d array) of GameObjects with the same type into one layer.
Level
Level class represents a game level and contains all information for that game level.
LevelManager
LevelManager class as game manager to take charge of loading, arranging levels and sets of levels for user to choose and play.
LevelSetScreen
LevelSetScreen class as type of SCREEN view when user intends to select a set to play.
LevelSetScreenController
LevelSetScreenController class to register and handle event of the LevelSetScreen.
Logger
Logger class takes charge of logging different levels of console message for each GameManager.
Main
Main class for the program to run.
MusicManager
MusicManager class as game manager to take charge of loading, arranging levels and sets of levels for user to choose and play.
Player
Player class as GameObject, possessing PlayerDirection and PlayerStatus enumeration.
Player.PlayerDirection
PlayerDirection enumeration defines all facing direction of Player object.
Player.PlayerStatus
PlayerStatus enumeration defines all status of Player object.
PlayerController
PlayerController class implementing EventHandler to handle all user input when playing gaming.
PopUpScreen
PopUpScreen class is the second level hierarchy abstract class of the GameScreen representing a new pop up screen instead of a screen shown by stage of ScreenPlayer.
QuitGamePopUp
QuitGamePopUp class as type of POP_UP_SCREEN view when user intends to quit the game.
ResourceManager
ResourceManager class as game manager to take charge of loading, storing and transferring resources when running the game.
ScoreBoardPopUp
ScoreBoardPopUp class as type of POP_UP_SCREEN view when user complete a level.
ScoreBoardPopUpController
ScoreBoardPopUpController class to register and handle event of the ScoreBoardPopUp.
ScoreBoardScreen
ScoreBoardScreen class as type of SCREEN view when user intends to check all high-score records.
ScoreBoardScreenController
ScoreBoardScreenController class to register and handle event of the ScoreBoardScreen.
ScoreRecord
ScoreRecord class as to store information of high scores of each level.
ScreenPlayer
ScreenPlayer class takes charge of initializing game views by given type of screens.
StartScreen
StartScreen class as type of SCREEN view as home page of the app.
StartScreenController
StartScreenController class to register and handle event of the StartScreen.
Utils
Utility class for the facilitate other operation of the program, containing reusable and stateless helper methods and fields.
VictoryScreen
VictoryScreen class as type of SCREEN view when user completed all levels of a set.
VictoryScreenController
VictoryScreenController class to register and handle event of the VictoryScreen.
ViewAdapter
ViewAdapter class takes charge of initializing game views that are pop-up screen type.
ViewPlayer
ViewPlayer interface to be implemented by ScreenPlayer and ViewAdapter to initialize screens(Stage).
Wall
Wall class as GameObject, possessing WallStatus enumeration.
Wall.WallStatus
WallStatus enumeration defines all status of Wall object.
